---
import Layout from "../../components/layout/BaseLayout.astro"

const lastUpdated = "May 9, 2026"
---

<Layout
    lang="en"
    title="Cookie Policy - Javier Piedra"
    description="Information about cookie usage on jpiedra.com."
>
    <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8 py-32 lg:py-40">
        <header class="mb-16">
            <p
                class="text-xs font-body font-medium tracking-[0.3em] text-accent uppercase mb-6"
            >
                Legal information
            </p>
            <h1
                class="font-heading text-[clamp(2rem,4.5vw,3.5rem)] leading-[1.1] text-text-primary mb-6"
            >
                Cookie Policy
            </h1>
            <p class="text-sm text-text-muted font-body">
                Last updated: {lastUpdated}
            </p>
        </header>

        <div
            class="legal-content flex flex-col gap-10 text-text-primary font-body leading-relaxed"
        >
            <section>
                <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl mb-4">1. What are cookies</h2>
                <p>
                    Cookies are small text files that a website stores in the
                    user's browser when visited. They allow recognizing the user
                    on subsequent visits, remembering preferences, or collecting
                    information about browsing activity.
                </p>
                <p class="mt-4">
                    This policy describes which cookies are used on jpiedra.com
                    and for what purpose, in compliance with Article 22.2 of
                    Spanish Law 34/2002 on Information Society Services and
                    Electronic Commerce (LSSI-CE) and the General Data
                    Protection Regulation (GDPR).
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl mb-4">
                    2. Cookies used on this website
                </h2>
                <p>
                    This website has been designed to minimize cookie usage and
                    respect user privacy as much as possible. Specifically:
                </p>
                <ul class="mt-4 list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                    <li>
                        <strong
                            >No tracking, analytics, or advertising cookies are
                            used.</strong>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong
                            >No social media or third-party cookies are used for
                            commercial purposes.</strong>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Web fonts are served from the website's own domain,
                        without transferring data to external services.
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <p class="mt-4">
                    The hosting provider (<strong>Netlify, Inc.</strong>) may
                    use strictly technical cookies to ensure the proper
                    functioning of the site, such as those related to load
                    balancing or content delivery. These cookies are necessary
                    for the provision of the service and, in accordance with
                    Article 22.2 of the LSSI-CE, do not require prior user
                    consent.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl mb-4">
                    3. Types of cookies by purpose
                </h2>
                <p>
                    For informational purposes, the cookies that may be used on
                    any website are typically classified into the following
                    categories:
                </p>
                <ul class="mt-4 list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                    <li>
                        <strong>Technical cookies:</strong> necessary for the operation
                        of the website. They do not require consent.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Personalization cookies:</strong> allow remembering
                        user preferences (language, region, etc.).
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Analytics cookies:</strong> collect information about
                        site usage to measure performance. They require consent.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Advertising cookies:</strong> display personalized
                        ads based on the user's profile. They require consent.
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <p class="mt-4">
                    <strong
                        >Only strictly necessary technical cookies are used on
                        jpiedra.com.</strong
                    >
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl mb-4">
                    4. How to manage cookies
                </h2>
                <p>
                    Although this site does not use cookies that require
                    consent, the user can configure their browser at any time to
                    accept, reject, or delete stored cookies. Management depends
                    on the browser used:
                </p>
                <ul class="mt-4 list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                    <li>
                        <a
                            href="https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/95647?hl=en"
                            target="_blank"
                            rel="noopener noreferrer"
                            class="text-accent underline underline-offset-2"
                            >Google Chrome</a>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <a
                            href="https://support.mozilla.org/en-US/kb/enhanced-tracking-protection-firefox-desktop"
                            target="_blank"
                            rel="noopener noreferrer"
                            class="text-accent underline underline-offset-2"
                            >Mozilla Firefox</a>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <a
                            href="https://support.apple.com/guide/safari/manage-cookies-sfri11471/mac"
                            target="_blank"
                            rel="noopener noreferrer"
                            class="text-accent underline underline-offset-2"
                            >Apple Safari</a>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <a
                            href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoft-edge/delete-cookies-in-microsoft-edge-63947406-40ac-c3b8-57b9-2a946a29ae09"
                            target="_blank"
                            rel="noopener noreferrer"
                            class="text-accent underline underline-offset-2"
                            >Microsoft Edge</a>
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <p class="mt-4">
                    Disabling technical cookies may affect the proper
                    functioning of certain parts of the website.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl mb-4">
                    5. Changes to the cookie policy
                </h2>
                <p>
                    This cookie policy may be updated to reflect legislative,
                    technical, or service changes. The date of the last update
                    is shown at the beginning of the document. Users are advised
                    to review this policy periodically.
                </p>
                <p class="mt-4">
                    For any inquiries regarding this policy, please contact <a
                        href="mailto:contacto@jpiedra.com"
                        class="text-accent underline underline-offset-2"
                        >contacto@jpiedra.com</a
                    >.
                </p>
            </section>
        </div>
    </article>
</Layout>
